9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 197, L.D. 297, “An Act Regarding the
10 Management of Oversized Bulky Waste from Wastewater Treatment Plants”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act Regarding the Management of Wastewater Treatment Plant Sludge at the
13 State-owned Landfill'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and before the
15 emergency clause and inserting the following:
16 'Sec. 1. 38 MRSA §1310-N, sub-§5-A, ¶B, as amended by PL 2023, c. 517, §5,
17 is further amended by amending subparagraph (2) to read:
18 (2) A solid waste processing facility that generates residue requiring disposal shall
19 recycle or process into fuel for combustion through methods other than chemical
20 plastic processing all waste accepted at the facility to the maximum extent
21 practicable, but in no case at a rate less than 50%. For purposes of this subsection,
22 "recycle" does not include chemical plastic processing and does include, but is not
23 limited to, plastic-to-plastic recycling; the reuse of waste generated within the State
24 as defined in section 1303‑C, subsection 40‑A, paragraph C; the recovery of metals
25 from waste; the use of waste or waste-derived product as material substitutes in
26 construction; and the use of waste as boiler fuel substitutes.
27 At least 50% of the waste that a solid waste processing facility characterizes as
28 recycled under this subparagraph must have been reused or recycled by the facility
29 through methods other than placement of the waste in a solid waste landfill, except
30 that a solid waste processing facility that was in operation during calendar year
31 2018, that accepts exclusively construction and demolition debris and that accepted
32 more than 200,000 tons of such debris in calendar year 2018 shall:
33 (a) Reuse or recycle at least 15% of such debris through methods other than
34 placement in a solid waste landfill by July 1, 2024 2026;
